    "body": "1. The go garbage collector doesn't immediately return the allocated memory to the OS, it just signals that if the OS should need it, it can be returned. \r\n2. A cache of `4Gb` means that geth will actively make use of 4G, it doesn't constrain geth to not use more in case there is more available. ",
